The paper discusses measures of computational complexity and inductive inference, which are topics commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). The introduction of physical measures such as volume and energy suggests a possible connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and systems and control theory (cs.SY).
